---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CopyPrompt from "../components/CopyPrompt.astro";

const setupPrompt = `Set up this repo to use srid/agency by following the instructions at
https://github.com/srid/agency/blob/master/docs/agency-setup.md`;

const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<BaseLayout title="agency">
  <header class="topbar">
    <span class="topbar-mark">srid<span class="slash">/</span>agency</span>
    <a href="https://github.com/srid/agency" rel="noopener">github ↗</a>
  </header>

  <section class="hero wrap">
    <h1 class="hero-mark">agency<span class="dot">.</span></h1>
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">a workflow for coding agents</p>

    <p class="hero-slogan">
      a loop you can<br />
      <span class="accent-magenta">leave alone.</span>
    </p>

    <p class="hero-tag">
      Two skills. <code class="cmd-cyan">/talk</code> for design.
      <code class="cmd-magenta">/do</code> for shipping. End-to-end, every diff.
    </p>

    <CopyPrompt text={setupPrompt} />
  </section>

  <section class="sec wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">01</span>
      <div>
        <p class="sec-label">the loop</p>
        <h2 class="h2"><span class="accent-cyan">/talk</span> to design, <span class="accent-magenta">/do</span> to ship.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pair">
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-cyan">/talk &nbsp;·&nbsp; spec isn't obvious</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">Sketch first. Ship later.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          Discuss, read, sketch. Run <code>/hickey</code> + <code>/lowy</code> on
          the sketch. Read-only. Hand the converged plan to
          <code class="cmd-magenta">/do</code>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-magenta">/do &nbsp;·&nbsp; "done" is concrete</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">Research → review → ship.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          Implement. Run <code>/hickey</code> + <code>/lowy</code> +
          <code>/code-police</code> on the diff. CI, merge. Each fix lands as
          its own commit.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body" style="margin-top: 2.25rem;">
      <p>
        <strong><code class="cmd-magenta">/do</code> has no design phase.</strong>
        Pasting a thin plan into <code class="cmd-magenta">/do</code> produces a
        thin implementation. The fix is to do the design work in
        <code class="cmd-cyan">/talk</code> first.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">02</span>
      <div>
        <p class="sec-label">feedback</p>
        <h2 class="h2">no e2e tests, <span class="accent-cyan">no autonomy.</span></h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <p>
        E2e tests are a prerequisite, not a nice-to-have. Unit tests and
        type-checks alone don't tell the agent whether its change actually
        worked.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ul class="triple" style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
      <li class="triple-cell is-magenta">
        <p class="triple-label">frontend</p>
        <p class="triple-body">
          Screenshot evidence on every PR.
          <a href="https://github.com/srid/agency/issues/106" rel="noopener">#106</a>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="triple-cell is-cyan">
        <p class="triple-label">nix infra</p>
        <p class="triple-body">
          NixOS VM tests. Closest thing to an executable spec the agent can
          drive.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="triple-cell is-lime">
        <p class="triple-label">backend / library</p>
        <p class="triple-body">
          Fast, deterministic e2e. 30s deterministic beats 10min thorough.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="sec wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">03</span>
      <div>
        <p class="sec-label">structural review</p>
        <h2 class="h2">tests catch correctness. <span class="accent-magenta">/do catches design.</span></h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <p>
        After implementing, <code class="cmd-magenta">/do</code> runs two design
        reviews in parallel against the actual diff. Each finding lands as its
        own commit; the full ledger ships as a PR comment.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pair">
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-magenta">/hickey</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">Catches accidental complexity.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          After Rich Hickey's <em>Simple Made Easy</em>. Flags the
          complecting that tests pass straight through.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-cyan">/lowy</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">Checks where the seams sit.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          After Juval Lowy's <em>Righting Software</em>. Module boundaries
          should encapsulate axes of change, not just functionality.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body" style="margin-top: 2.25rem;">
      <p>
        Full framing:
        <a href="https://kolu.dev/blog/hickey-lowy/" rel="noopener">Hickey/Lowy on kolu.dev</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="sec wrap">
    <div class="sec-head">
      <span class="sec-num">04</span>
      <div>
        <p class="sec-label">scope</p>
        <h2 class="h2">one PR, <span class="accent-lime">end to end.</span></h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="body" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
      <p>
        Each <code class="cmd-magenta">/do</code> run lands a single PR — start
        to finish in one sitting. No cross-PR memory by design. Larger work
        gets broken into phases by <code class="cmd-cyan">/talk</code>, then
        shipped one PR per phase.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="pair">
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-lime">within the PR</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">Step state lives in <code>.do-results.json</code>.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          Per-step lifecycle, status, and timing. The
          <code>do-stop-guard</code> hook reads it so the agent can't bail
          while a run is still <code>working</code>.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="pair-cell">
        <p class="pair-marker is-magenta">across PRs</p>
        <p class="pair-headline">A phased issue is the cross-PR memory.</p>
        <p class="pair-body">
          Branches that linger past a day or two are a smell — break the work
          smaller. For multi-phase work, <code class="cmd-cyan">/talk</code>
          writes the phased issue, <code class="cmd-magenta">/do</code> consumes
          one phase per PR.
          <a href="https://github.com/juspay/kolu/issues/514" rel="noopener">kolu#514</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="foot wrap">
    <p class="colophon">
      <a href="https://github.com/srid/agency" rel="noopener"
        >github.com/srid/agency</a
      >
      <span>·</span>
      <a href="https://kolu.dev" rel="noopener">sister · kolu.dev</a>
      <span>·</span>
      <span>mit · {year}</span>
    </p>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
